abstract: Sunday’s Super Bowl broadcast on Fox attracted an average TV audience of 99.9 million, 1.7% above last year, the Los Angeles Times said on Monday, citing Nielsen ratings data.
snippet: Sunday’s Super Bowl broadcast on Fox attracted an average TV audience of 99.9 million, 1.7% above last year, the Los Angeles Times said on Monday, citing Nielsen ratings data.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Sunday’s Super Bowl broadcast on Fox attracted an average TV audience of 99.9 million, 1.7% above last year, the Los Angeles Times said on Monday, citing Nielsen ratings data.
headline_main: Super Bowl TV Audience Up 1.7% From Last Year as Viewers Tune In for More Than Just Football
headline_print_headline: Super Bowl TV Audience Up 1.7% From Last Year as Viewers Tune In for More Than Just Football

abstract: In a speech last month to farmers in Texas, President Donald Trump won applause as he talked up recent U.S. trade agreements. When he tried to boast of his administration's ethanol policy, however, he was met with silence.
snippet: In a speech last month to farmers in Texas, President Donald Trump won applause as he talked up recent U.S. trade agreements. When he tried to boast of his administration's ethanol policy, however, he was met with silence.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — In a speech last month to farmers in Texas, President Donald Trump won applause as he talked up recent U.S. trade agreements. When he tried to boast of his administration's ethanol policy, however, he was met with silence.
headline_main: Iowa's Anger Over Trump's Ethanol Policy Gives Democrats Opening
headline_print_headline: Iowa's Anger Over Trump's Ethanol Policy Gives Democrats Opening

abstract: The U.S. Senate impeachment trial of Donald Trump is now in its final stages, with senators devoting Tuesday to short speeches laying out their positions on whether the president should be acquitted or convicted on charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.

abstract: The U.S. Democratic presidential nominating race got off to a slow and rocky start in Iowa on Monday, as the results of the state's caucuses were delayed for hours while party officials double-checked "inconsistencies" in the initial count.
snippet: The U.S. Democratic presidential nominating race got off to a slow and rocky start in Iowa on Monday, as the results of the state's caucuses were delayed for hours while party officials double-checked "inconsistencies" in the initial count.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — The U.S. Democratic presidential nominating race got off to a slow and rocky start in Iowa on Monday, as the results of the state's caucuses were delayed for hours while party officials double-checked "inconsistencies" in the initial count.
headline_main: Democratic Presidential Race Off to Rocky Start as Iowa Results Delayed by 'Inconsistencies'
headline_print_headline: Democratic Presidential Race Off to Rocky Start as Iowa Results Delayed by 'Inconsistencies'

abstract: Scores of volunteers from across the United States descended on icy Iowa ahead of Monday's Democratic caucus with one goal: nominating a candidate who can defeat Republican President Donald Trump in November.

headline_main: Volunteers Flock to Iowa for High-Stakes Democratic Nominating Contest
headline_print_headline: Volunteers Flock to Iowa for High-Stakes Democratic Nominating Contest

abstract: Republican U.S. Senator Lisa Murkowski, an unpredictable moderate in a polarized Washington, on Monday declared she will vote to acquit Donald Trump, but not before leveling an attack against the president and fellow lawmakers of both parties during a partisan impeachment ordeal.

abstract: Like many Iowans, Peggy Magner is still grappling with a weighty choice as the state's first-in-the-nation nominating contest fast approaches: which Democratic candidate is best equipped to defeat Republican President Donald Trump in November.

abstract: The European Union expressed regret on Tuesday that the United States has decided to use anti-personnel landmines more widely and once again considers them to be an important weapon of war.
snippet: The European Union expressed regret on Tuesday that the United States has decided to use anti-personnel landmines more widely and once again considers them to be an important weapon of war.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — The European Union expressed regret on Tuesday that the United States has decided to use anti-personnel landmines more widely and once again considers them to be an important weapon of war.
headline_main: EU Regrets US Military Policy About-Face on Landmines
headline_print_headline: EU Regrets US Military Policy About-Face on Landmines

abstract: Iowa's Democrats promised to begin to release long-delayed results on Tuesday afternoon from the party's chaotic first voting in its process of picking a candidate to face Republican Donald Trump in November's U.S. presidential election.

headline_main: Iowa Democrats to Release First Results After Presidential Caucus Chaos
